## Installation

```bash
# Linux/macOS (binary)
curl -sL https://github.com/wesbragagt/gps/releases/latest/download/gps-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m) -o gps
chmod +x gps
sudo mv gps /usr/local/bin/

# Go install
go install github.com/wesbragagt/gps/cmd/gps@latest

# Verify
gps --version
```

## Advanced Usage with jq

```bash
# Get entry points as JSON array
gps -f json | jq '.project.key_files.entry_points[]'

# Count files by type
gps -f json | jq '.project.stats.by_type'

# Get project type
gps -f json | jq -r '.project.type'

# List all test files
gps -f json | jq '.project.key_files.tests[]'

# Check if entry points exist (for CI)
gps -f json | jq '.project.key_files.entry_points | length'
```

## Tips for Copilot

1. **Start minimal, expand as needed** - Use `--summary` first, then `-L 2`, then focus deeper
2. **Use --no-meta for structure-only** - When file sizes/lines aren't relevant
3. **Combine flags for efficiency** - `gps -L 2 -d --no-meta` for ultra-minimal directory tree
4. **Exclude noise** - `gps -I "node_modules,dist,build"` for cleaner output
5. **Use --focus for large projects** - Reduces tokens by 70-90% when analyzing specific areas

## Quick Reference

```bash
gps                    # Default TOON output
gps -L 2               # 2 levels deep
gps --summary          # Project overview only
gps --entry-points     # Find entry points
gps --focus src/       # Focus on directory
gps --no-meta          # Skip metadata
gps -f json            # JSON output
gps -I "node_modules"  # Exclude patterns
gps -P "*.go"          # Include only Go files
gps -e go,md,yaml      # Include extensions
gps --exclude-ext log,tmp  # Exclude extensions
gps --tokens           # Show token count
```
